Sankey Thingy

A visualization of a group of papers - in this case all papers from the OC database from some authors. The categories are based on the SJR "area" of a journal. The left column are categories of referenced papers, the middle column is where papers are published and the right one is where the ones citing papers are cited.

A bunch of randomly selected authors + CÃ©sar from the crossref database.

Of course normally there shouldn't be +60 of them on the same page, but the performance seems to hold up. Unless you tinker with the padding or iterations...
